:'''Dongsheng:''' Sure! {{MC|f=Big sister|m=Big brother}}, what do you wish to talk about?
:<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_502011302_392-->
:<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_502011302_392-->
:{{DIcon|Talk}} Tell me about this celestial lady.
::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502113103-->
::'''Dongsheng:''' The celestial lady? I grew up with her stories as bedtime tales! It's a long story...
::'''Dongsheng:''' Our village is next to a place called Redspring Peak. Our lives were really hard. We'd go an entire year without eating a single chicken drumstick.
::'''Dongsheng:''' We were some backwater village. The only thing we did was plant crops that don't get enough water to grow, or hunt for hares and rats to keep ourselves fed.
::'''Dongsheng:''' On top of this tough life, we also have demons rampaging in the mountain. It's like rubbing salt in the wound. It made life really really difficult.
::'''Dongsheng:''' Legends say that long before I was born, the northernmost star in the sky suddenly shone so brightly that it turned night into day.
::'''Dongsheng:''' Some older villagers who knew about the stars said a constellation was about to descend to rid of evil. And then, five or six years later, an egg suddenly fell from the sky!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} An egg?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502113109-->
:::'''Dongsheng:''' The story said it was an egg, so it must've been an egg. This egg cracked open, and out came a beautiful lady.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502113112-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502113112-->
:::'''Dongsheng:''' Laiwang said his great-grandfather's great-grandfather was hunting in the woods that day and was the first to see the scene. The egg cut out a ravine on the mountain that extended a few dozen miles, and the whole forest caught on fire.
:::'''Dongsheng:''' Everyone thought the celestial lady was beautiful and nice, but there was something wrong with her head. When she first arrived, she couldn't even talk in a complete sentence. The most well-read elder gave her a name...
:::'''Dongsheng:''' ...Eggborn. Then one day, the celestial lady suddenly began to speak like a human. She said, "you can call me Mufang." Everyone was afraid of offending a celestial, so they called her "Goddess Mufang" instead.
::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} The celestial lady?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502113111-->
:::'''Dongsheng:''' Yes. This egg cracked open and out popped a beautiful lady.
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_502113112-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_502113112-->
:::'''Dongsheng:''' Laiwang said his great-grandfather's great-grandfather was hunting in the woods that day and was the first to see the scene. The egg cut out a ravine on the mountain that extended a few dozen miles, and the whole forest caught on fire.
